definition: to say/to tell/to announce/to report/to denounce/to file a lawsuit/to sue
to succeed through failure/to achieve one's final aim despite apparent setback
pinyin: yi3 shi1 bai4 er2 gao4 zhong1

sentences.english: Lyon claim that Chelsea's attempts to sign midfielder Michael Essien have all but collapsed.
sentences.chinese: 里昂宣稱切爾西試圖簽下中場埃辛的事情以失敗告終。

sentences.english: The argument culminated in a fist fight.
The cause they contrived so painstakingly also ended in failure.
sentences.chinese: 他們慘淡經營的事業也以失敗而告終。

sentences.english: Her persuasions were to no avail. （end in a failure）
sentences.chinese: 她的勸說以失敗而告終。

sentences.english: Getting involved in power struggles with your child will end up with tears from someone or maybe both of you.
sentences.chinese: 與孩子做鬥爭最後會以一方甚或雙方的淚眼而告終。

sentences.english: This first attempt was scrapped and another moon was chosen.
sentences.chinese: 首次嘗試以失敗告終，然而另一顆“月明”已被選佳。

sentences.english: Be nice to nerds . Chances are you'll end up working for one.
sentences.chinese: 成爲書呆子很好，機遇以你爲什麼工作的方式而告終。

sentences.english: Emotional antisemitism, he wrote, merely ended in pogroms.
sentences.chinese: 他寫道，情感上的反猶太主義將以大屠殺而告終。

sentences.english: Because of her findings, the movent to end the powerful monopolies was greatly sengthened.
sentences.chinese: 由於她的發現，大大加強告終束獨有壟斷運動的權勢。

sentences.english: My debut in the sixth-grade class production was a failure.
sentences.chinese: 我在六年級的初次登場就以失敗告終。

sentences.english: Does this mean the end of films opening with a lion’s roar?
sentences.chinese: 這是否意味着影片開頭的獅子吼就此告終？

sentences.english: Honda has settled the strikes at its other two factories as well.
sentences.chinese: 本田旗下另兩起罷工，均以廠方息事寧人告終。

sentences.english: A quarrel only, with two people cry on each other's shoulder ended a noon.
sentences.chinese: 唯一的一次吵架，以兩個人抱頭痛哭一中午而告終。

sentences.english: The first televised debate between candidates for the chancellorship was judged a draw last night.
sentences.chinese: 昨晚競選長官職位的第一場電視辯論以平局告終。

sentences.english: That’s actually why we ended up selling the company.
sentences.chinese: 其實那便是我們以出售公司而告終的原因。

sentences.english: Many of these first attempts at correcting the spinal deformity ended in disaster.
sentences.chinese: 許多最初的矯正脊柱畸形的嘗試都以失敗告終。
